------------------------------------------------
Introduction to Node JS
    * open source
    * cross platform
    * JS runtime environment
    * Very performant
        - Runs the V8 JS engine core of Google Chrome outside of the browser
    * Runs in a single process instead of creating thread for every request
    * libraries in Node JS written in Non-Blocking paradigm
    * Used for server side & light weight
    * Application = Data intensive Real time application
        - Event driven & Non-Blocking I/O model
        - eg: Video streaming, one page application.....
Install Node JS
Run js file using Node command in terminal